                    <span>I really enjoyed this next book from Debbie.  It solidifies what she talks about in her first book - owning the side of ourselves that we want to forget exists.  Remember, the people around you know all your faults - but what is a fault to one is not a fault to another.  By not owning all of ourselves, we deprive the world and those closest to us the opportunity to see who they really are!  This book was worth the money, and I will read it over and over again.</span>
                  
